article_title: Health insurance marketplace plans cover many previously uninsured, survey finds
article_text:
Health insurance marketplace plans cover many previously uninsured, survey finds

Photo: Kaiser Family Foundation Nearly six in 10 people who bought marketplace health insurance...

More than half of the people who bought coverage in the health insurance marketplace under the Affordable Care Act had been previously uninsured, according to a new survey by the Kaiser Family Foundation.

article_metadata.description: More than half of the people who bought coverage in the health insurance marketplace under the Affordable Care Act had been previously uninsured, according to a new survey by the Kaiser Family Foundation.  The foundation, a private, nonprofit organization focused on health care analysis, found almost six in 10 people who purchased marketplace plans had been uninsured before obtaining coverage.  For months, critics of the health care law have questioned whether many previously uninsured people would buy health insurance, speculating that insured people more likely were using the marketplace to shop for and buy less expensive coverage.
article_metadata.author.name: By Lora Hines
